96
00:06:01,429 --> 00:06:03,762
narrator: today we can listen to music instantly       

97
00:06:03,764 --> 00:06:06,164
from a smartphone or in our car,         

98
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:08,366
but to enjoy a bit of nostalgia,

99
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:11,036
you can still enjoy a more tactile and visual   

100
00:06:11,038 --> 00:06:14,172
musical experience by pushing down a button    

101
00:06:14,174 --> 00:06:16,374
and waiting for a jukebox to load            

102
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:18,844
and play a song on a vinyl record.       

103
00:06:22,449 --> 00:06:28,653
this classic 1940s dome-top jukebox is built by hand.   

104
00:06:28,655 --> 00:06:30,022
it plays vinyl records,    

105
00:06:30,024 --> 00:06:33,058
which are loaded into the machine after purchase.  

106
00:06:36,998 --> 00:06:38,931
a technician builds the cabinet

107
00:06:38,933 --> 00:06:42,001
out of thin, flexible sheets of plywood.          

108
00:06:42,003 --> 00:06:44,937
once five sheets of wood have been glued together,   

109
00:06:44,939 --> 00:06:48,807
the technician places them in a dome-shaped mold.     

110
00:06:48,809 --> 00:06:52,144
after glue is applied to the inside of the cabinet, 

111
00:06:52,146 --> 00:06:55,814
team members insert the wood back panel.      

112
00:06:55,816 --> 00:06:57,683
the layers are then held together         

113
00:06:57,685 --> 00:07:00,886
by hydraulic rams for 24 hours.

114
00:07:00,888 --> 00:07:03,956
then workers remove the cabinet
from the mold         

115
00:07:03,958 --> 00:07:06,825
and install shelving and brackets.         

116
00:07:06,827 --> 00:07:09,894
the brackets, or knuckles, are made out of zinc      

117
00:07:09,896 --> 00:07:12,898
and will hold the cabinet door together.   

118
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:14,966
when a knuckle comes out of the mold,     

119
00:07:14,968 --> 00:07:18,170
the edges are rough and contain excess metal,   

120
00:07:18,172 --> 00:07:21,974
so a technician smoothes the knuckle with a belt sander 

121
00:07:21,976 --> 00:07:25,044
and then uses a guide to drill screw holes.     

122
00:07:28,849 --> 00:07:32,785
the factory sends the knuckles 
out to a specialty metal plater,

123
00:07:32,787 --> 00:07:34,520
who plates them with chrome.  

124
00:07:37,924 --> 00:07:42,127
the cabinet door consists of a front hoop and a front panel.

125
00:07:42,129 --> 00:07:45,264
technicians place both parts in an assembly jig       

126
00:07:45,266 --> 00:07:48,400
to ensure they are positioned correctly.     

127
00:07:48,402 --> 00:07:50,469
then eight knuckles are connected --        

128
00:07:50,471 --> 00:07:54,673
two at the top and three on each side.    

129
00:07:54,675 --> 00:07:57,476
every jukebox is uniquely handmade,       

130
00:07:57,478 --> 00:08:00,545
so a technician verifies that the door and cabinet   

131
00:08:00,547 --> 00:08:02,614
are aligned accordingly.    

132
00:08:02,616 --> 00:08:06,418
next, both components are moved
to the cabinet-finishing area 

133
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:10,622
to be painted or stained, depending on the wood.     

134
00:08:10,624 --> 00:08:13,358
the customer selects the color and any options,        

135
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:15,827
such as programmable l.e.d. lighting        

136
00:08:15,829 --> 00:08:19,198
or bluetooth connectivity for streaming digital music.  

137
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:26,104
the bubble tubes are handcrafted
from standard glass tubing.  

138
00:08:26,106 --> 00:08:28,573
an artisan seals the tube at the bottom         

139
00:08:28,575 --> 00:08:32,111
then passes a probe to check for any small cracks. 

140
00:08:32,113 --> 00:08:33,846
if the tube is intact,     

141
00:08:33,848 --> 00:08:37,316
tiny silicon crystals are placed at the bottom,   

142
00:08:37,318 --> 00:08:40,185
and fluid that turns from liquid into gas      

143
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:44,056
is poured into the tube at very low temperature.    

144
00:08:44,058 --> 00:08:46,658
the artisan melts the glass with a torch          

145
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:49,661
to seal the top of the tube.  

146
00:08:49,663 --> 00:08:52,731
each jukebox has four straight bubble tubes          

147
00:08:52,733 --> 00:08:54,799
and four curved ones.     

148
00:08:54,801 --> 00:08:58,070
making a curved tube requires two artisans.     

149
00:08:58,072 --> 00:08:59,671
one heats the tube,      

150
00:08:59,673 --> 00:09:02,875
while the other bends it around a form.         

151
00:09:02,877 --> 00:09:05,344
next, the tubes are placed in a tester,          

152
00:09:05,346 --> 00:09:08,680
which heats the fluid, turning it into gas.      

153
00:09:08,682 --> 00:09:10,749
the silicon crystals at the bottom         

154
00:09:10,751 --> 00:09:12,985
disrupt the gas as it rises,  

155
00:09:12,987 --> 00:09:15,554
creating hundreds of rising bubbles.       

156
00:09:15,556 --> 00:09:18,023
as the bubbles reach the top of the tube,      

157
00:09:18,025 --> 00:09:20,492
they cool and turn back into liquid.   

158
00:09:20,494 --> 00:09:22,427
a technician installs the tubes

159
00:09:22,429 --> 00:09:25,630
inside transparent protective covers.       

160
00:09:25,632 --> 00:09:28,233
he connects each tube to a heating plate       

161
00:09:28,235 --> 00:09:31,436
hidden inside the cabinet.   

162
00:09:31,438 --> 00:09:32,838
another specialist wires    

163
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:37,643
the jukebox electrical systems and speakers.         

164
00:09:37,645 --> 00:09:40,579
the speaker assembly is located
behind the front door     

165
00:09:40,581 --> 00:09:43,448
of the cabinet.        

166
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:48,387
a 1950s-style jukebox is made with shaped glass and chrome. 

167
00:09:48,389 --> 00:09:50,856
it has a curved, see-through front door,    

168
00:09:50,858 --> 00:09:54,660
which allows the user to watch as the vinyl system finds,   

169
00:09:54,662 --> 00:09:57,496
pulls, and plays the selected record.      

170
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:03,335
each machine contains a 70-slot circular basket   

171
00:10:03,337 --> 00:10:05,337
that holds a two-sided record. 

172
00:10:08,142 --> 00:10:10,742
the motor in this reproduction jukebox is guided       

173
00:10:10,744 --> 00:10:12,877
by computer software.     

174
00:10:12,879 --> 00:10:16,214
the motor rotates the basket to bring the selected record  

175
00:10:16,216 --> 00:10:17,749
to the lift arm.        

176
00:10:17,751 --> 00:10:21,553
another motor rotates the turntable to play the song.

177
00:10:21,555 --> 00:10:24,223
the software reads the position
of each record         

178
00:10:24,225 --> 00:10:28,827
via an optical sensor and a rotating slotted disc.  

179
00:10:28,829 --> 00:10:31,096
the software calculates the quickest route       

180
00:10:31,098 --> 00:10:32,764
to the requested record,    

181
00:10:32,766 --> 00:10:37,102
then spins the basket to bring the record to the lift arm.  

182
00:10:37,104 --> 00:10:39,104
so when your jukebox arrives, 

183
00:10:39,106 --> 00:10:42,174
all you have to do is drop in your favorite records,     

184
00:10:42,176 --> 00:10:45,176
make title cards using the labeling software,  

185
00:10:45,178 --> 00:10:48,046
and insert them in the title display.     

186
00:10:48,048 --> 00:10:51,716
this jukebox is ready to provide
the listener with good times  

187
00:10:51,718 --> 00:10:54,386
and good vibes for many years to come.    

188
00:11:01,662 --> 00:11:07,199
