189
00:11:07,201 --> 00:11:10,068
narrator: standard excavators shovel and dig,        

190
00:11:10,070 --> 00:11:11,336
but due to their size,     

191
00:11:11,338 --> 00:11:14,806
they can sometimes break underground utilities.     

192
00:11:14,808 --> 00:11:17,009
vacuum excavators dig with a technique        

193
00:11:17,011 --> 00:11:18,744
that doesn't cause damage,   

194
00:11:18,746 --> 00:11:21,880
softening the soil with    
a high-pressure stream of water,

195
00:11:21,882 --> 00:11:24,716
then sucking up the mud into a debris tank.      

196
00:11:28,889 --> 00:11:30,756
a vacuum excavator functions  

197
00:11:30,758 --> 00:11:34,226
as a pressure washer and shop vacuum.        

198
00:11:34,228 --> 00:11:36,161
using a high-pressure water jet,

199
00:11:36,163 --> 00:11:39,765
the excavator removes materials
with a vacuum hose       

200
00:11:39,767 --> 00:11:42,634
and deposits it into a debris tank.      

201
00:11:42,636 --> 00:11:46,704
the tank holds up to 1,188 gallons of debris    

202
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:49,507
and is made from high-strength sheet steel.   

203
00:11:49,509 --> 00:11:54,446
a steel rolling machine curves the sheet under pressure.   

204
00:11:54,448 --> 00:11:57,382
a welder clamps the ends of the sheet together 

205
00:11:57,384 --> 00:11:59,718
and tacks them to form a cylinder.      

206
00:12:03,957 --> 00:12:07,592
next, he transfers the cylinder
to a welding fixture      

207
00:12:07,594 --> 00:12:10,996
and fully welds the seam.   

208
00:12:10,998 --> 00:12:13,131
then the welder mounts a steel dome          

209
00:12:13,133 --> 00:12:15,067
to the front end of the tank. 

210
00:12:17,471 --> 00:12:21,473
using an assembly jig, he clamps
the dome into position.    

211
00:12:21,475 --> 00:12:27,945
♪          

212
00:12:27,947 --> 00:12:30,015
he strikes the dome with a mallet         

213
00:12:30,017 --> 00:12:33,418
to close any gaps between the dome and the cylinder.   

214
00:12:35,756 --> 00:12:38,357
he tack-welds the parts to each other.         

215
00:12:43,029 --> 00:12:45,497
he removes the cylinder from the jig          

216
00:12:45,499 --> 00:12:49,101
and fully welds the exterior seam around the perimeter.   

217
00:12:51,238 --> 00:12:54,039
another machinist welds the inner seam.        

218
00:12:57,711 --> 00:13:01,112
other components are welded to the tank.          

219
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:04,649
these include a large hinge for the tank's rear door,   

220
00:13:04,651 --> 00:13:08,720
side pins that allow the tank to tilt when emptied,     

221
00:13:08,722 --> 00:13:11,856
a pair of windows, storage hooks,         

222
00:13:11,858 --> 00:13:15,127
and an inlet for the suction hose.     

223
00:13:15,129 --> 00:13:18,530
once all the steel parts    
have been cleaned with hot water

224
00:13:18,532 --> 00:13:20,865
and a chemical that inhibits rust,      

225
00:13:20,867 --> 00:13:23,302
a technician sprays them with primer.          

226
00:13:25,405 --> 00:13:28,940
then a coat of durable, epoxy-based paint is applied. 

227
00:13:28,942 --> 00:13:31,543
the paint takes a couple of hours to dry.   

228
00:13:34,548 --> 00:13:38,416
the vacuum excavator is built into a welded steel trailer  

229
00:13:38,418 --> 00:13:41,219
that has upright steel posts on each side          

230
00:13:41,221 --> 00:13:43,888
to hold the water tanks.    

231
00:13:43,890 --> 00:13:46,557
a technician installs l.e.d. brake lights      

232
00:13:46,559 --> 00:13:48,627
and side indicator lights.   

233
00:13:51,365 --> 00:13:54,633
next, wiring is run along the length of the trailer.   

234
00:13:54,635 --> 00:13:57,302
the wires control the machine's
trailer brakes         

235
00:13:57,304 --> 00:13:59,237
and safety lights.       

236
00:13:59,239 --> 00:14:03,508
then the wiring is connected to the lights.         

237
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:05,510
a technician covers every connection        

238
00:14:05,512 --> 00:14:07,312
with heat-shrink plastic.   

239
00:14:07,314 --> 00:14:11,516
this will ensure the connected wires are water-resistant.   

240
00:14:11,518 --> 00:14:14,586
next, the hydraulic pump is installed,         

241
00:14:14,588 --> 00:14:16,188
as well as rubber cushions   

242
00:14:16,190 --> 00:14:18,657
to protect the bottom of the debris tank,      

243
00:14:18,659 --> 00:14:23,261
and reflective red-and-white  
safety tape, as required by law.

244
00:14:23,263 --> 00:14:26,131
a technician installs two industrial tires      

245
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:28,400
on each side of the trailer.  

246
00:14:28,402 --> 00:14:31,336
he runs hydraulic lines from the hydraulic pump    

247
00:14:31,338 --> 00:14:34,539
to the lift cylinders that tilt the debris tank   

248
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:36,875
and to its rear-door mechanism.

249
00:14:40,013 --> 00:14:44,282
the empty debris tank weighs more than 1,500 pounds.    

250
00:14:44,284 --> 00:14:46,083
using an overhead crane,    

251
00:14:46,085 --> 00:14:48,553
a team lifts and positions the tank            

252
00:14:48,555 --> 00:14:50,756
over the rear part of the trailer,        

253
00:14:50,758 --> 00:14:55,159
lowering it into the hydraulic lift system.   

254
00:14:55,161 --> 00:14:57,295
next, the power pack is installed          

255
00:14:57,297 --> 00:14:58,896
on the front of the trailer.  

256
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:01,633
the pack contains the gas or diesel engine,   

257
00:15:01,635 --> 00:15:04,335
the vacuum and water pumps, the battery,          

258
00:15:04,337 --> 00:15:07,639
and belts that connect the pumps and engine pulleys. 

259
00:15:07,641 --> 00:15:10,575
after the first of two polyethylene water tanks    

260
00:15:10,577 --> 00:15:14,111
are assembled, technicians install an air-filtration unit.

261
00:15:14,113 --> 00:15:19,250
the unit protects the inner components of the vacuum pump. 

262
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:21,987
two technicians install the second water tank,     

263
00:15:21,989 --> 00:15:25,924
placing it in between the trailer's support posts.  

264
00:15:25,926 --> 00:15:30,862
then the tank is secured with two crossbars.      

265
00:15:30,864 --> 00:15:32,864
to dig with a vacuum excavator,

266
00:15:32,866 --> 00:15:35,800
the suction hose is attached to the debris tank       

267
00:15:35,802 --> 00:15:37,936
while the other end digs.   

268
00:15:37,938 --> 00:15:42,406
then the ignition, water, and vacuum pumps are started. 

269
00:15:42,408 --> 00:15:45,877
the water pump pressurizes   
the water flowing from the tanks

270
00:15:45,879 --> 00:15:49,747
through the hose and out the nozzle of an attached wand.

271
00:15:49,749 --> 00:15:52,551
the water pressure turns the soil into mud,       

272
00:15:52,553 --> 00:15:56,020
and the suction hose removes the material.     

273
00:15:56,022 --> 00:15:58,422
thanks to this shovel-free process,   

274
00:15:58,424 --> 00:16:02,461
operators can now dig without damaging underground utilities.

275
00:16:09,770 --> 00:16:15,507
♪          

276
00:16:15,509 --> 00:16:17,576
narrator: inside a pewter shaving set  

277
00:16:17,578 --> 00:16:20,445
is a double-barreled mug called scuttle.        

278
00:16:20,447 --> 00:16:24,048
in one compartment, it keeps shaving water hot,  

279
00:16:24,050 --> 00:16:26,518
while holding soap in the other.

280
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:28,853
the set's badger-bristle shaving brush         

281
00:16:28,855 --> 00:16:32,457
is used to work the soap and water into a hot lather.  

282
00:16:36,329 --> 00:16:38,063
with a pewter shaving set,   

283
00:16:38,065 --> 00:16:42,133
the user employs nostalgic tools
to shave.           

284
00:16:42,135 --> 00:16:45,537
it's elegant, and it helps get the job done. 

285
00:16:48,342 --> 00:16:50,141
pewter of made of tin,     

286
00:16:50,143 --> 00:16:53,277
with a small amount of copper and antimony.    

287
00:16:53,279 --> 00:16:56,948
tin is a soft metal, while the other metals add strength. 

288
00:16:59,286 --> 00:17:01,486
a metal worker places a filter gate         

289
00:17:01,488 --> 00:17:03,121
at one end of the mold.    

290
00:17:06,293 --> 00:17:08,293
he scoops up molten pewter   

291
00:17:08,295 --> 00:17:12,364
and pours it in the mold in front of the filter gate.  

292
00:17:12,366 --> 00:17:14,766
the filter gate captures impurities      

293
00:17:14,768 --> 00:17:19,103
as the pewter flows to the other side.       

294
00:17:19,105 --> 00:17:22,307
heat causes any air pockets to rise to the surface     

295
00:17:22,309 --> 00:17:23,641
and dissipate.         

296
00:17:23,643 --> 00:17:25,844
spraying the pewter with cool water        

297
00:17:25,846 --> 00:17:28,513
accelerates the solidification.

298
00:17:28,515 --> 00:17:32,717
after 10 seconds, the pewter has
hardened into a thick slab   

299
00:17:32,719 --> 00:17:35,320
called an ingot.        

300
00:17:35,322 --> 00:17:37,989
a metal worker breaks off the excess material      

301
00:17:37,991 --> 00:17:39,924
left by the filter gate.    

302
00:17:39,926 --> 00:17:44,528
the pewter is now in a workable form.      

303
00:17:44,530 --> 00:17:49,133
a technician places the ingot in a machine with steel rollers

304
00:17:49,135 --> 00:17:52,904
and adjusts the space between the upper and lower rollers.  

305
00:17:55,208 --> 00:17:59,944
using 66 tons of pressure, the rollers flatten the ingot. 

306
00:17:59,946 --> 00:18:02,213
it takes several passes through the rollers      

307
00:18:02,215 --> 00:18:05,116
to reduce the ingot to its desired thickness.   

308
00:18:07,887 --> 00:18:10,722
additionally, the rolling stretches the ingot,      

309
00:18:10,724 --> 00:18:13,491
transforming it into a large sheet.      

310
00:18:13,493 --> 00:18:16,428
later, the sheet will be used to make the shaving scuttle  

311
00:18:16,430 --> 00:18:18,496
and brush handle.       

312
00:18:18,498 --> 00:18:22,299
now it's time to construct the beard combs.        

313
00:18:22,301 --> 00:18:26,104
a technician ladles molten pewter into a rubber mold.   

314
00:18:26,106 --> 00:18:29,106
the centrifugal force forces the liquid pewter    

315
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:31,309
into the mold's crevices.   

316
00:18:31,311 --> 00:18:34,713
after 2 1/2 minutes, the mold is removed,      

317
00:18:34,715 --> 00:18:39,184
producing seven pewter beard combs.      

318
00:18:39,186 --> 00:18:42,053
the technician extracts the combs from the runners   

319
00:18:42,055 --> 00:18:43,922
formed from the molten pewter. 

320
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:49,794
after sanding, the combs are dipped      

321
00:18:49,796 --> 00:18:51,730
in a specialized solution.   

322
00:18:55,469 --> 00:18:56,868
in a vibrating machine,    

323
00:18:56,870 --> 00:19:01,138
the ceramic pellets shake off most of the excess solution.  

324
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:04,875
but the solution that's seeped into the embossed logo remains,

325
00:19:04,877 --> 00:19:06,511
adding definition.       

326
00:19:09,682 --> 00:19:12,417
back to the shaving scuttle and brush assembly,      

327
00:19:12,419 --> 00:19:15,387
a large sheet of pewter is cut into discs.       

328
00:19:17,958 --> 00:19:20,492
a technician pours resin into a mold          

329
00:19:20,494 --> 00:19:23,294
to create the shaving-brush handle.   

330
00:19:23,296 --> 00:19:26,431
after the handle's cured for 25 minutes,        

331
00:19:26,433 --> 00:19:29,767
the resin transitions from a liquid to a solid.   

332
00:19:29,769 --> 00:19:32,637
now he has a handle form to work with.         

333
00:19:32,639 --> 00:19:34,972
as the handle spins in a lathe,

334
00:19:34,974 --> 00:19:37,174
the technician shaves off imperfections    

335
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:38,576
with a cutting tool.      

336
00:19:40,714 --> 00:19:44,983
a sharp, circular die cuts out discs from the pewter sheet.  

337
00:19:49,656 --> 00:19:52,056
with the handle core still spinning,        

338
00:19:52,058 --> 00:19:54,058
the worker shapes the pewter disc,        

339
00:19:54,060 --> 00:19:56,795
essentially giving the part a pewter skin.         

340
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,933
using the same spinning techniques,          

341
00:20:02,935 --> 00:20:07,271
the scuttle shaving mug are now complete.       

342
00:20:07,273 --> 00:20:10,141
using a natural abrasive mixed with oil,        

343
00:20:10,143 --> 00:20:12,343
the pewter parts are buffed.  

344
00:20:12,345 --> 00:20:18,082
this step removes flaws and provides an initial polish.

345
00:20:18,084 --> 00:20:22,086
then the maker's mark is carved
into the shaving-scuttle base, 

346
00:20:22,088 --> 00:20:26,291
stamping the logo into the pewter.        

347
00:20:26,293 --> 00:20:30,027
now that the scuttle-mug parts are assembled,         

348
00:20:30,029 --> 00:20:32,764
a technician solders the base to the scuttle body.      

349
00:20:32,766 --> 00:20:37,902
♪          

350
00:20:37,904 --> 00:20:41,039
a decorative cured handle adds visual interest        

351
00:20:41,041 --> 00:20:43,441
and will provide the user a place to grip.        

352
00:20:46,046 --> 00:20:47,645
a technician adds more solder 

353
00:20:47,647 --> 00:20:50,915
to seal the handle to the scuttle body.      

354
00:20:50,917 --> 00:20:53,518
this shaving scuttle is now complete.        

355
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:56,521
all the parts will undergo an extensive polishing,    

356
00:20:56,523 --> 00:21:00,858
giving the pewter a mirror finish.        

357
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:02,260
using a buffing wheel,     

358
00:21:02,262 --> 00:21:06,064
a technician polishes the shaving scuttle one last time. 

359
00:21:08,535 --> 00:21:14,072
finally, this pewter shaving set
is ready to take on stubble.  

